---
notes: These sweet potato brownies are rich and decadent!
servings: 4
source_url: "https://cooking.nytimes.com/recipes/1023412-skillet-chicken-thighs-with-brown-butter-corn"
time: 30 minutes
---

Chop @garlic{3 cloves} and @yellow onion{1}. Chop @basil(1/3 cup). Cover skillet with @butter{2 tbsp} and soften 2-4 minutes. Season @chicken thighs{1 lb} with @paprika, salt, and pepper, and sear on medium heat about 8-10 minutes each side. Remove the chicken. Melt the remaining @butter{1 tbsp}, and then add @corn{1 can} rinsed and saute corn for 2 - 5 minutes. Add the chicken back to the skillet and cook for another 10-12 minutes until fully the meat is fully cooked. Squeeze half of the @lime{1} and slice the other half. Add the lime wedges to the skilled and top with chopped @basic. 
